
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to concatenate strings to construct a SQL statement for adding a foreign key constraint to a table. It uses the [strings.concat] slot to combine static strings with dynamic values retrieved from the [.arguments] node, specifically [tableName], [columnName], [foreignTable], and [foreignField], to form a complete SQL command. The resulting string is a SQL statement that alters a table to add a foreign key referencing another table's column.
strings.concat
   .:"alter table "
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/tableName
   .:" add foreign key ("
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/columnName
   .:") references "
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/foreignTable
   .:(
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/foreignField
   .:)
